From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Li Hua Qian <huaqian.li@siemens.com>
Date: Wed, 22 Jul 2026 11:16:56 +0800
Subject: [PATCH] arm64: dts: ti: iot2050: Keep SPI NOR in SPL

SPL device-tree pruning can remove the SPI NOR child while retaining the
Cadence QSPI controller. The controller then lacks the flash properties
needed to probe the boot device, causing SPI boot to fail on bus 0.

Mark the SPI NOR node bootph-pre-ram so SPL retains its compatible,
chip-select, and timing properties without retaining it in later boot
phases unnecessarily.

Signed-off-by: Li Hua Qian <huaqian.li@siemens.com>
---
 dts/upstream/src/arm64/ti/k3-am65-iot2050-common.dtsi | 1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

diff --git a/dts/upstream/src/arm64/ti/k3-am65-iot2050-common.dtsi b/dts/upstream/src/arm64/ti/k3-am65-iot2050-common.dtsi
index 9f3824555ab0..bd870bea4ce3 100644
--- a/dts/upstream/src/arm64/ti/k3-am65-iot2050-common.dtsi
+++ b/dts/upstream/src/arm64/ti/k3-am65-iot2050-common.dtsi
@@ -500,6 +500,7 @@
 		cdns,tchsh-ns = <60>;
 		cdns,tslch-ns = <60>;
 		cdns,read-delay = <2>;
+		bootph-pre-ram;
 
 		partitions {
 			compatible = "fixed-partitions";
